	"metadata": {
		"title": "libtiff: Out-of-memory issue in TIFFReadEncodedStrip() may lead to Denial of Service (moderate)",
		"reference": [
			{
				"ref_id": "CVE-2024-6716",
				"ref_url": "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2024-6716",
				"source": "CVE"
			}
		],
		"description": "DOCUMENTATION: The MITRE CVE dictionary describes this issue as: A flaw was found in libtiff. This flaw allows an attacker to create a crafted tiff file, forcing libtiff to allocate memory indefinitely. This issue can result in a denial of service of the system consuming libtiff due to memory starvation. \n            STATEMENT: This issue can be triggered by the TIFFReadFromUserBuffer function. An application that does not use this function is not vulnerable to this vulnerability.\n            MITIGATION: Applications that do not parse files from untrusted or malicious sources will not be vulnerable to this vulnerability.",
